The directive stuff I worked on is in the incant tabs file that I have been using for offline work and testing. I wrote two short incant actions. One to replace text (which is an improvement on tok directives that cannot); and one to insert before or after a buffer line that contains a match on some match text you provide in the directive. That too is better than tok directive that can only match the beginning of a line. OTOH, tok directives are idempotent; incant directives are not, unless you work on a copy of the file you are applying directives to. Have not come up with a way to fix that.
One advantage of the incant directives, not only can you insert large blocks of text, you can replace large blocks with other large blocks; nice if you want to replace a set of actions with a revised set of actions or some such.
