If source is a buffer and a directiveField argument has three fields in its list: source fromBody toBody. fromBody and toBody are strings (use of doc text fields may be called for). Normal use would have fromBody match text in source: text to be matched could look like a C++ label: or a //comment,
    or no reason the fromBody match could not be a block of text spanning multiple lines. The doc block feature used in grammarOnTheFly could be applied in fromBody for that purpose
    Once a fromBody match is found, the fromBody text is replaced by the toBody text
    Using source=getFile(filename); source text can be loaded from a file;
    if fromBody IN source; is true and sets source mark as side effect (it does)
    and source -= fromBody; deletes fromBody.count characters in source starting at mark
    and source += text; inserts text at buffer mark
    then BYU
Note: fromBody IN source will start looking from source.mark if it is set, otherwise it starts looking from source.start. If you want to make sure source search starts from start, unMark(source); first.
